OL,3,C'The ocean is overflowing': UN chief
OL,4,Cissues warning about Pacific sea level
OL,5,Crise
OL,7,FSea surface temperatures in the
OL,8,FSouthwest Pacific have risen three
OL,9,Ftimes faster than the global average
OL,10,Fsince 1980, according to the World
OL,11,FMeteorological Organization's State of
OL,12,Fthe Climate report.
OL,14,FIt also found marine heat waves have
OL,15,Fdoubled in frequency and become more
OL,16,Fintense and longer lasting.
OL,18,FThe ocean is "undergoing changes which
OL,19,Fwill be irreversible for centuries to
OL,20,Fcome," said WMO Secretary-General
OL,21,FCeleste Saulo.
